main event: An observation of possible rocket exhaust or a meteor at Elmendorf AFB, Alaska on January 18, 1956.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for only 0.08 seconds., Observers noted a color change from yellow to orange., The object appeared to be the size of a half dollar and was seen flying at a flight level to the horizon., Another similar sighting occurred on the same date but with a different flight path from west to east., The initial evaluation suggested it could be a meteor passing into Earth's atmosphere.
witness description: Control tower operator at Elmendorf AFB, considered completely reliable.
